entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: A decentralized operating system or platform. It seems to be a successor or evolution of AI16Z, with a focus on Solana as its native chain and cross-chain functionality.

entities.name: AI16Z
entities.description: An existing token that is undergoing a migration to the ElizaOS token. It is the predecessor or current version of ElizaOS tokens.

entities.name: Solana
entities.description: A high-performance public blockchain platform known for its speed and low transaction costs. It utilizes a Proof-of-History (PoH) consensus mechanism in addition to Proof-of-Stake (PoS).

entities.name: CCIP
entities.description: Cross-Chain Interoperability Protocol, a standard or system used to enable communication and asset transfer between different blockchain networks.

entities.name: Ethereum
entities.description: A decentralized, open-source, public blockchain system that features smart contract functionality. It is the second-largest blockchain by market capitalization and is known for its smart contract capabilities.

entities.name: Base
entities.description: A layer-2 scaling solution built on top of the Ethereum blockchain, developed by Coinbase. It aims to provide lower transaction fees and faster confirmation times.

entities.name: BNB Chain
entities.description: A decentralized blockchain network developed by the cryptocurrency exchange Binance. It consists of BNB Beacon Chain (for governance and staking) and BNB Smart Chain (for smart contracts and dApps).

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control using Git that offers distributed version control and source code management (SCM) functionality. It is widely used for software development and collaboration.

entities.name: x402
entities.description: An emerging ecosystem or standard that ElizaOS is integrating with, particularly for agent messaging and payment capabilities.

entities.name: DegenAI
entities.description: A token that will coexist with the ElizaOS token after the migration. It is suggested by some community members to be currently undervalued.

entities.name: PayAI
entities.description: An entity that the ElizaOS team has identified a security threat related to, involving fake accounts running airdrop scams. The team plans to inform PayAI about the situation.

entities.name: Spartan Arena
entities.description: A project related to trading bots or LLMs competing in trading, indicating expansion into the algorithmic trading space.

entities.name: Rati AI
entities.description: An entity that has filed a trademark, as announced in the ElizaOS community discussions.

entities.name: Web3 authentication
entities.description: A method or flow for authenticating users within decentralized applications, typically involving the use of cryptocurrency wallets.

entities.name: Coinbase
entities.description: A cryptocurrency exchange platform and one of the largest major exchanges globally. It also develops and supports blockchain technologies.

entities.name: Polygon
entities.description: A blockchain scaling solution that provides an easy-to-use interface for developers to build and launch DApps and other blockchain-based projects. It aims to improve scalability and reduce transaction fees on Ethereum.

entities.name: WuAI
entities.description: A platform for launching AI agents that replicate a user's digital footprint, with plans to integrate x402.
